‚öñÔ∏è XI. ARREST LAYER INTEGRATION

KeeperVault does not merely detect intrusions.
It identifies, isolates, and builds a complete forensic case ‚Äî automatically.

Once an intrusion or violation is confirmed, the Arrest Layer activates.

1. Tripwire Activation

Silent signals detect unauthorized commands, devices, or patterns.
When tripped, the system begins recording the intruder‚Äôs every action in real time ‚Äî including device ID, IP signature, command string, and access path.

2. Honeypot Containment

The intruder is silently redirected into a simulated environment.
Every file, interface, and system response is fake ‚Äî but behaves authentically enough to hold the attacker.
All actions taken inside are recorded, time-stamped, and cryptographically sealed.

3. Quarantine Isolation

The compromised device or process is cut off from all active nodes.
Local interfaces freeze, remote tunnels collapse, and network ports close.
No outbound data escapes; no internal data is altered.

4. Forensic Capture

KeeperVault‚Äôs internal VaultBots notarize every event.
Keystrokes, commands, and data requests are recorded into immutable, timestamped audit chains.
This ensures unbroken chain of custody for legal prosecution.

5. Tiered Escalation Path

Depending on the system classification:

Civilian Systems ‚Üí Report packet prepared for local law enforcement or cybercrime units.

Corporate Systems ‚Üí Logs transferred to internal Legal & Compliance captains.

Critical Infrastructure ‚Üí Alerts sent to designated site security or partner agency.

Defense Systems ‚Üí Immediate relay to national command or security operations.

Every escalation is sealed under Vault signature, signed by both local captain and KeeperVault system root.

